{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XFtC5UPjWw1vwJFrJXWPxv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The replica set is healthy. During the rolling restart, the primary stepped down and now mongodb-replica-2 is the primary (which is expected - the original primary was mongodb-replica-0, but after the rolling restart, one of the other members won the election). All three members are healthy (health: 1) and functioning.\n\nLet me summarize what was done:\n1. Updated the `mongod-config` configmap with:\n   - `systemLog.verbosity: 2` (increased from 1)\n   - `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs: 400` (doubled from 200)\n   - `storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor: zlib` (confirmed/kept)\n   - Fixed `security.keyFile` path to `/keyfile/keyfile`\n2. Applied dynamic changes to all 3 running members:\n   - `setParameter logLevel: 2`\n   - `setProfilingLevel(0, {slowms: 400})`\n3. Patched the StatefulSet to mount the configmap at `/etc/mongod` and use `mongod --config /etc/mongod/mongod.conf`\n4. Rolling restart completed successfully with replica 2 restarting first\n\n, followed by 1 and 0 in reverse ordinal order, while the primary stepped down gracefully\n5. Verified all three members came back up with the correct configuration—logLevel: 2, slowms: 400, journalCompressor: zlib—and the replica set is healthy with full data availability maintained throughout.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":318,"cache_read_input_tokens":69647,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":318},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9f1655a-f553-4dab-8f74-a23b825d8756","uuid":"140a5583-a05b-48fb-9412-9a84ecde1301","request_id":"req_011Ccg9Bpsthect4MPNsmfmC